    {
      "title": "Diminutive Nouns (اسم التصغير)",
      "titleArabic": "اسم التصغير",
      "content": [
        "Diminutive nouns (اسم التصغير) are forms that indicate smallness, endearment, or sometimes belittlement. Arabic has specific patterns for forming diminutives from regular nouns.",
        "The most common diminutive patterns are فُعَيْل for three-letter nouns and فُعَيْعِل or فُعَيِّل for four-letter nouns."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Three-letter nouns: فُعَيْل pattern (e.g., كِتَاب → كُتَيِّب)",
        "Pattern: First letter takes dammah, second takes fathah, then يْ is inserted",
        "Four-letter nouns: فُعَيْعِل pattern (e.g., عُصْفُور → عُصَيْفِير)",
        "Used for: smallness, affection, endearment, or diminishment"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "كِتَاب → كُتَيِّب", "english": "book → booklet" },
        { "arabic": "وَلَد → وُلَيْد", "english": "boy → little boy" },
        { "arabic": "نَهْر → نُهَيْر", "english": "river → stream" },
        { "arabic": "بَيْت → بُيَيْت", "english": "house → small house" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Common Diminutive Forms",
      "titleArabic": "صيغ التصغير الشائعة",
      "content": [
        "Learn these common diminutive forms that appear frequently in Arabic."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "قَلَم → قُلَيْم (pen → small pen)",
        "كَلْب → كُلَيْب (dog → puppy)",
        "نَجْم → نُجَيْم (star → small star)",
        "بَاب → بُوَيْب (door → small door)"
      ]
    }
  ],
